  research_stream = {trp-pentamer-vascular},
  note     = {High-speed AFM + cryo-EM. Discovers TRPV3 can form pentamers (not only canonical tetramers) in dynamic equilibrium via membrane diffusive protomer exchange. Pentamer shows ~2.4-fold enlarged pore at selectivity filter, subunit 18-degree hinge motion, and ~3-minute average lifetime. DPBA agonist significantly increases pentamer frequency. Explains the long-known pore-dilation phenomenon (increased large-cation permeability after prolonged activation). First demonstration of non-tetrameric stoichiometry in a TRP channel with functional consequence. Certainty: High for structural finding; implications for other TRP channels (TRPM3, TRPV1) in ME/CFS are speculative extrapolations.}
}

