  note         = {Narrative review. Immunosenescence (aging immune cells) drives chronic inflammation impairing mitochondrial ATP production and promoting muscle catabolism in ME/CFS. HPA-axis suppression and beta2-adrenergic dysfunction amplify immune problems. Cross-organ communication sustains fatigue. Proposed biomarkers: cytokines and immune exhaustion markers. Comprehensive Physiology. ME/CFS relevance: directly applies immunosenescence framework to ME/CFS fatigue mechanism — links ANS dysfunction, immune aging, and energy failure.}
}

