  research_stream = {epigenetics-mecfs},
  certainty    = {0.62},
  note         = {Comprehensive review (Frontiers in Endocrinology 2025).
                  PTPRN2 (IA-2beta/phogrin) is a pseudophosphatase expressed
                  throughout neuroendocrine tissues (hypothalamus, pituitary,
                  pancreatic islets, hippocampus, neurons broadly). Required
                  for normal accumulation of neurotransmitters norepinephrine,
                  dopamine and serotonin in the brain. Required for normal
                  accumulation of secretory vesicles in hippocampus and pituitary.
                  Double KO: PTPRN2 deletion impairs kisspeptin neuron development
                  with female-specific impaired ovulation. PTPRN2 suppresses
                  melanotroph proliferation/POMC expression. Can dephosphorylate
                  PI(3)P and PI(4,5)P2 (functional significance debated).
                  RELEVANCE: broad neuroendocrine role explains why hypomethylation
                  (potentially altered expression) could impact cognitive and
                  autonomic symptoms in ME/CFS.}
}

